arts.ttl: Port Vale’s winless run extended after Cheltenham stalemate
arts.sum: Vale have not won for eight League Two games.

arts.ttl: Brentford forward Ashley Hay completes loan move to Cheltenham Town
arts.sum: Brentford B team head coach Neil MacFarlane said on the move : “Ash came to us from Hitchin Town and we saw some excellent qualities we felt we could develop and, over a sustained period of time, we have worked together to put him in the best possible position to go and succeed on loan. His arrival at Brentford followed a standout season with the Southern Premier Division Central side during the 2022/23 campaign, where he netted 11 goals.

arts.ttl: Cheltenham Town sign "best right-back in League of Ireland" as "warrior" Darragh Power joins after leaving Waterford
arts.sum: Cheltenham Town have completed the signing of right-back Darragh Power from League of Ireland Premier Division club Waterford FC on an 18-month deal. In September (second last month of the season), Darragh had over 184 duels won.

arts.ttl: Preview: Port Vale vs. Cheltenham Town - prediction, team news, lineups
arts.sum: Sports Mole previews Wednesday's League Two clash between Port Vale and Cheltenham Town, including predictions, team news and possible lineups.
